b6-4b40-aa7a-6dd68939f9b4","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Origin of Brazilian Portuguese"},"id":"f8ccc71b-108b-4737-a9e5-1a6c11303936","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["<a href=\"/why-brazil-doesnt-speak-spanish\">Portugal colonized Brazil</a> in the 1500s. At that time, Tupinamba or Tupi for short was combined with Portuguese as the official language of the colony. Tupi was banned, so the people were required to strictly speak Portuguese, but adapted a few words from Tupi and other local languages."]},"id":"d8faa458-ba86-4c5f-9813-8785b87109cc","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"When the Differences Began to Rise"},"id":"eff553a3-529e-49e7-9369-2e2c8b77ab37","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["In the 18th century, more differences appeared between the European or Standard Portuguese from the Brazilian Portuguese. The French influence brought about the changes in Portugal, and the Italian and other European immigrants to Brazil influenced the Brazilian Portuguese.","Later on, in the 20th Century, More differences came about due to the new technological words. The Europeans did not have a uniform procedure for adapting words. In contrast, the Brazilians were eager to adapt the new words and embraced the use of idiomatic expressions."]},"id":"72974c3c-80bc-4c44-a924-0a31a161ed1b","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Portuguese In Africa, Asia and Oceania"},"id":"d2de1a6d-6199-4e0c-af32-4a330da74a70","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The Portuguese in these regions are categorized into Creole and non–Creole forms. Creole is a mixture of local African languages with Portuguese. They are commonly considered a different language due to the differences between the two.","Angola and Mozambique are the first places in Africa where Portuguese became the spoke language mixed with other local languages. A lot of dialects are close to that of European Portuguese, but some parts do resemble Brazilian Portuguese.","Portuguese is a language rich in history and through past colonization and mixing with local languages has evolved extensively since the 12th century."]},"id":"3bd510f0-dbb0-4b18-a9f2-d223f51f3c54","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Works Cited"},"id":"43fbea58-d600-41a3-99c0-226b2b996bcd","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Delta Translator USA. (2006). The Portuguese Language. Delta Translator USA. Retrieved August 25, 2006, from http://www.deltatranslator.com/port_lang.htm","Zdravko Batzarov. (n.d.). General Overview of the Portuguese language. Retrieved August 25, 2006, from http://www.orbilat.com/Languages/Portuguese/Portuguese.html","At TopTenREVIEWS We Do the Research So You Don’t Have To.™"]},"id":"6cf67789-1eda-4c09-910d-73aa42ee8b75","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"article_page_221","url":"/where-did-the-portuguese-language-come-from","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"tiffany-stone","url":"/author/tiffany-stone","dateCreated":"2019-04-18T08:03:59Z","name":"Tiffany Stone","dateModified":"2019-04-18T08:03:59Z","id":"hREcUd2zefU3tRnVr2iJTF","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"1970-01-01T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"2016-09-30T18:47:48Z","name":"Where Did the Portuguese Language Come From?","synopsis":"When people are asked where Portuguese is spoken, they usually respond with Portugal or Brazil.","review":{},"strapline":"When people are asked where Portuguese is spoken, they usually respond with Portugal or Brazil.","language":"en","dateModified":"2016-09-30T18:47:48Z","id":"Wj2ijv5ayFETtfkp96iJPN","meta":{"title":"Where Did the Portuguese Language Come From?","description":"When people are asked where Portuguese is spoken, they usually respond with Portugal or Brazil. They do not think about the countries in Africa such as Angola, Mozambique, Angola and Cabo Verde or"},"products":[],"dateImported":"2019-04-18T08:05:26Z","type":"feature","template":"standard","social":{"twitter":{"image":{"status":"","height":0,"path":"/nxM86T57PMYbGGhwn